title: Frieze, 1890–1920
description: A repeating pattern of scrolled cartouches containing a tulip flower and stem connected to a smaller similar design on a dotted background of simple flowers and larger dots giving way at the top to flowers and larger dots. Bordered by horizontal bands at the top and at the bottom by repeating tulip flower and horizontal bands. Printed in white, gold, gray and pale gray.

tombstone.epitaph:
Frieze, 1890–1920.
1890–1920. Machine-printed on machine-made paper. Gift of Victorian Collectibles. 1979-91-55.
